Quote:  From January 11 to March 11, 1870, the miners of Naseby went on strike, and finally induced the `water squatters' to lower their rates from five pounds a  `Hogburn' head to two pounds. [fn] A `Hogburn' head was the stream of water which would run through a box 17 inches wide by 1 inch in depth with 5 inches of  pressure. - J.J.T., `Otago Daily Times,' July 25,

1932.
